<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-04-01T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-04-01T02:00:00-05:00" n="276" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6125: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-01T15:00:00+08:00">April 1, 1933—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 1—9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>299. Legation’s 295.<note n="86" xml:id="d276fn86">March 31, 10 a.m.,
                                    <ref target="#pg_263">p. 263</ref>.</note> Following from
                            Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“March 31, 4 p.m. According to information from a reliable source
                                    the treaty referred to in my telegram of March 30, 3 p.m.,
                                    provides for the transfer to Japanese control of the Manchukuo
                                    telephone, telegraph and wireless systems.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>